WS0SCBTP.description: Zero wait-states inserted with the Suppressed Conditional Branch Target Prefetch (SCBTP) function enabled. SCBTP saves energy by delaying the Cortex' conditional branch target prefetches until the conditional branch instruction is in the execute stage. When the instruction reaches this stage, the evaluation of the branch condition is completed and the core does not perform a speculative prefetch of both the branch target address and the next sequential address. With the SCBTP function enabled, one instruction fetch is saved for each branch not taken, with a negligible performance penalty.

FREE.description: When started, the LETIMER counts down until it is stopped by software.

ONESHOT.description: The counter counts REP0 times. When REP0 reaches zero, the counter stops.

BUFFERED.description: The counter counts REP0 times. If REP1 has been written, it is loaded into REP0 when REP0 reaches zero. Else the counter stops

DOUBLE.description: Both REP0 and REP1 are decremented when the LETIMER wraps around. The LETIMER counts until both REP0 and REP1 are zero

NONE.description: LETn_O0 is held at its idle value as defined by OPOL0.

TOGGLE.description: LETn_O0 is toggled on CNT underflow.

PULSE.description: LETn_O0 is held active for one LFACLKLETIMER0 clock cycle on CNT underflow. The output then returns to its idle value as defined by OPOL0.

PWM.description: LETn_O0 is set idle on CNT underflow, and active on compare match with COMP1

NONE.description: LETn_O1 is held at its idle value as defined by OPOL1.

TOGGLE.description: LETn_O1 is toggled on CNT underflow.

PULSE.description: LETn_O1 is held active for one LFACLKLETIMER0 clock cycle on CNT underflow. The output then returns to its idle value as defined by OPOL1.

PWM.description: LETn_O1 is set idle on CNT underflow, and active on compare match with COMP1
